# Lame nameserver for lame-nameserver.demo.
#
# The parent (demo. zone served by coredns-root) delegates this zone
# to ns1.lame-nameserver.demo. — but this container does NOT serve
# the zone authoritatively. It runs as a CoreDNS forwarder, so SOA
# queries against it return no authoritative answer; the exporter
# surfaces this as `dnshealth_query_success{check="soa",...}=0`.
#
# Originally specced as the "RA=1 advertised" demo (the recursion
# check should flag a server that ought to be authoritative-only but
# advertises recursion). That demo turned out to be infeasible with
# pure CoreDNS — the `forward` plugin doesn't reliably set the RA
# flag on referral responses without a real recursive upstream like
# unbound. See specs/004-demo-deployment/audit.md deviations #3 and
# #6 for the full reasoning. The "lame nameserver" failure mode this
# container actually demonstrates is equally real and arguably more
# common in the wild, so we kept it under a more honest name.

. {
    forward . 172.31.0.10:53
    cache 5
    log
    errors
}
